      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIFE IS YOURS (7) has a strong record this journey here with three wins and a minor from seven starts. In the money last time at Launceston (16.02) in a Grade 4, finishing a neck second. With a clean break looks hard to beat. TRICK (4) hit the ground running with a slick early sectional but ran over late and missed the frame when a 1.5 lengths fourth (19.65) over 340m at this track. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Can figure in the finish. DEADLY STREET (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (16.50) at Launceston behind Sherwood Boys in a Grade 5. Must be included in calculations. BLACKBRUSH GOLDY (2) is likely to have admirers.",
